The cavity was very deep under the old amalgam restoration. Mesial caries was diagnosed visually through the translucency of the mesial marginal ridge. The mesial caries was not clearly visible on the bitewing x-ray. A lot of times, interproximal caries can not be detected on a bitewing x-ray. 
TheraCal was placed as a liner and to mask the dark amalgam stains that could show through the translucency of the composite. 
The tooth was restored with Estelite Sigma Quick composite.
.
.

The patient is a dentist from Los Angeles, California. She wanted to save her tooth. 
1. All the caries were removed
2. Composite was placed on the tooth temporarily until the crown lengthening was done by a periodontist. 
3. After the crown lengthening, 2 metal posts were cemented with a resin cement and the tooth was built back with composite. 
4. Two retraction cords impregnated with epinephrine were placed before the final impression. 
5. A full zirconia crown (Bruxzir) was cemented using RelyX Luting 2.
.
.
